args: Whoa! Water's bubbling up out of the pot!\nWe're saved! The village is saved!
Indeed. I was so worried about what we\nwould do with this continual drought!\nI'll sleep well tonight, that's for sure!
Such a relief! Thank you, miss!
Don't mention it! We help each other\nout when times get tough!
Sounds like quite the commotion.\nI wonder what's going on?
M-my word! Look, over there—\nwater is flowing from that pot!
Yes, thanks to a young stranger from afar!

Our village has suffered severe drought,
but those days are behind us now.
All because of her ＂Qilin relic＂
or somesuch!
Those items are typically stewarded by\nsomeone of the Qilin tribe, yes?
Right. Which I guess means that this\nvillage was saved by them...?

Most unusual. Given the considerable
power the Qilin tribe possesses, they
generally abstain from involvement with
the world at large.
That's certainly the impression I've\ngotten from the other Qilin people\nwe've met.
I imagine they must have had a reason for\nhelping this village.
I just saw that people were in trouble,\nso I used my Qilin relic to help 'em!
What the—she's just a little kid!
When it comes to us Qilin, you can't judge\na book by its cover. We can stop the\naging process with our relics, y'know.
...Er, and that juicy little tidbit never\nleaves this room—er, village. Got it?!
If the folks back home heard I was spilling\nsecrets, they'd drag me back kicking\nand screaming!
Well, she certainly makes a rather...\ndifferent impression from past Qilin\nwe've met.
Well, there's all sorts,\neven among the Qilin.
Anyone who helps a person in need is all\nright in my book.
Hee hee! Stop, you're making me blush!\n...What's that? I'm a genius, you say?\nI mean it's true, but still!
Y'know, you seem all right! You got some\nkinda ulterior motive? Does it start with\n＂Qilin＂ and end with ＂relic,＂ maybe?
Welp, what can I do? If you insist,\nI'll let ya use 'em!
We made no such request. Moreover,\nshould Qilin relics really be used so\nfrivolously?

What's the problem? We Qilin have been
usin' our relics to live better lives since,
like, a gazillion years ago. Who are we
to monopolize 'em?!
If you ask me, we should be usin' 'em to\nhelp everybody lead happy, comfy lives!
I see your point, I suppose.
Yes! Someone who gets it!\nI knew I liked you!
I'll grant your any wish!\nWhere's your house? Lead the way!
Er, well, it's not so much a house as...
...Hee HEE! It's a CASTLE! And it's HUGE!
I thought you were pullin' my leg with all\nthis ＂prince＂ and ＂kingdom＂ stuff,\nbut this thing speaks for itself!
The girl's got a point! You don't exactly\nscream ＂royal,＂ {player_name}.
Ha ha, maybe not.\nSo, Jiang Ziya—
We have many people here, from my allies\nto people who came to us seeking aid.
Do you think you have anything that\ncould help them in their daily lives?
I'm sure I can rustle up something!
No... I'm just somewhat uneasy about\nthese Qilin relics. They sent the ancient\nQilin down the path of ruin, after all...
Right, and that's why they're so strict about\nmanaging them now.
But Jiang Ziya is Qilin herself; I think\nwe'll be all right.
She just wants everyone to be happy.\nI don't think someone like her is liable\nto have her heart corrupted by the relics.
...I suppose not. It seems I've let\nmy anxieties get the better of me.
In that case, Jiang Ziya—I know this is\nsudden, but might I make a request of\nyou?
The castle wall in that area over there has\nfallen into disrepair. Might you be able to\nrestore it with a relic?
Easy-peasy! I've got just the ticket—
If you throw this cloth over an object,\nit can be returned to its original state!

O power universal of the Qilin, be bound
by my solemn decree. Bond of causality,
course upstream through the natural order
and return worldly vessels to their root!
Hee hee ha ha hee! Perfection!\nGood as new, in the blink of an eye!
Wait, what was that? It sounded like...\nAh! The castle wall!

I tried to return the damaged bricks to
their original state, but they're going
back to their ORIGINAL original state...
As in, clay!
I totally forgot, but this cloth is\nsuuuuuper finicky!
Ugh, I am just the WORST with delicate\nstuff! Everyone, we have to repair the wall\ntogether! Gosh, I've really done it now...
You have certainly done something!\nNow hurry up and stop that relic!
